My best estimate treats this as:

- worldwide RHD passenger/light-car stock: roughly a couple hundred million, mainly Japan, UK, India, Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, Australia, South Africa, New Zealand, plus used Japanese RHD exports;
- share at least 10 years old: roughly mid-to-high 40%;
- orange share among older cars: about 0.6–0.8%, higher in Japan/UK/Australia, lower in India/SE Asia.

Multiplying those gives a central estimate a little above the threshold, so my single best guess is **760,000**.
